    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent.</hi> | (<hi rend="print">Railway Station | Orpington. S.E.R.</hi>)</placeName>
                    <date>December 28<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1881</date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I am much obliged for your letter. The statement about the beetle, probably a Staphylinus, hunting a worm by scent is quite new to me.—<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
                    <p>I have received another account of the noise made by worms, whilst dragging leaves into their burrows—<ref target="#foot.f2"/> —</p>
                    <p>Dear Sir | Yours faithfully &amp; obliged | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">0.1 (<hi rend="italic">Railway … S.E.R.</hi>)] <hi rend="italic">parentheses added</hi> </note>
            </div>

            
            
            
        </div>
        
        
        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">Baily’s letter has not been found. Although CD did not mention Baily’s observation, in <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_11418.xml"><hi rend="italic">Earthworms</hi> (1882)</ref>, p. 65, he did add that members of the beetle genera <hi rend="italic">Staphylinus</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Carabus</hi> attacked worms ferociously.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">CD had added information from <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_4364.xml">James Frederick Simpson</ref> on the rustling noise made by worms to the printing of the fifth thousand of <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2241.xml"><hi rend="italic">Earthworms</hi></ref>, p. 58 (see letters from J. F. Simpson, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-13459.xml">4 November 1881</ref> and <ref target="./DCP-LETT-13474.xml">8 November 1881</ref>).</note>
        </div>
    
